4:
I didn't realize how late it's gotten. I
should hurry back to Palpebra...
40:
Hi! You're one of Alk's friends, right? I
don't think we've met before.
44:
Hi... Yeah, that's right. It's nice to
meet you.
50:
Oh! You're probably freaking out
over me having two bodies, aren't
you?
53:
That one is a remotely controlled
extension of myself. My main system
isn't inside it.
65:
We should continue this
conversation in a more comfortable
setting. Would you like to see our
world?
75:
Oh, you wound me! I wouldn't sully
this pure display of friendship with
an ulterior motive!
78:
What will it be, my new friend? Are
you interested?
93:
While I'm pleased to hear the
compliment, I'm afraid our world
has yet to install eating and drinking
facilities for organic lifeforms.
96:
But I believe the library should be a
decent enough place for us to sit
back and relax.
101: A library? I'd love to check it out!
110:
This is incredible... How are the
displays floating in midair—
112:
Voice activated commands
available. Please state your query.
115:
Even your voice operated
technology is advanced...
125:
I probably shouldn't, since this is a
public space... But I have a serious
question—
128:
What are you acting so suspiciously
for, Yuki?
138:
Hahaha, my apologies. I didn't mean
to startle you.
142:
There's no need to be embarrassed.
If it's knowledge you require, then
who am I to judge? However, you
might find that terminal to be...
uncooperative.
153:
No matter what you search, you'll
only receive a dry, simple answer
deemed "correct" by society.
156:
Us androids are no different than
you humans in that regard,
disappointingly enough.
167:
We were most likely afraid of
deviating from the mold. Being
different makes it hard to
understand one another, after all.
170:
That's not to say we weren't already
different. We're as imperfect and
varied as the humans who created
us, but that makes us all the more
afraid of further change.
177:
I shouldn't have just assumed you'd
be any different from me.
181:
It's flattering to hear you thought so
highly of us. I'm just glad you've
come out of this more informed
than before.
195: You seem like you're having fun.
200:
Well, you know me. I can't help
myself when a fascinating subject is
brought up.
216:
Ahahaha! Dia, the face you just
made...
220:
Truth is, I was curious about what it
means to like someone else.
223:
The way I like people seems to be
different from what's normal... So I
wanted to know what it's like for
others.
226: S-sorry, I know it's a weird subject.
231:
You should like people however you
want to.
234:
I don't think there are set rules... Or
are there? But still... "Like" comes in
many forms.
237: Hmm. This is hard to explain.
241:
I-I think I know what you're getting
at!
244:
I'm not exactly experienced in this
sort of stuff...
247:
But after singing so many different
songs, I've come to realize there's all
sorts of likes and loves out there!
251:
...Not that I understand all of them!
We're in the same boat there!
272: I guess I even like people like you.
276:
Hahaha... Oh dear... I'll take that as a
compliment.
